21/09/2003
MAVROVO, Macedonia -- The western town of Mavrovo hosted a two-day seminar on developing interethnic co-operation. 
The event, which opened on Friday (19 September), was organised by the NGO Project for Ethnic Relations and the Swiss Embassy in Macedonia. 
Participants included Vice Prime Minister Musa Xhaferi, Minister of Local Government Aleksandar Gestakovski and Parliament Vice President Agron Buxhaku, as well as the Swiss, US, and NATO ambassadors to Macedonia.
In other news, the Macedonian Parliament resumed debate on a security report drafted by the opposition VMRO-DPMNE and the Liberal Party. 
Opposition leaders demand more decisive measures to resolve security problems involving criminal and terrorists groups. 
(MIA - 19/09/03)
